<br>
Instead I've decided that the appropriate argument is not pro-marijuana but rather anti-alcohol. Other than the money the industry rakes in via the sale of a admittedly addictive substance, I've yet to find anyone anywhere who can give me a legitimate reason why it's legal to consume something that can be directly associated with more than 40% of all vehicle related injuries in the US, half of all violent crimes and the death of one person every 30 minutes.<br>
<br>
Cog <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#242422><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub40.ezboard.com/bthesaryrntavern.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kryttosarcadiasaryrn>Kryttos Arcadia Saryrn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><span style='color:pink;'>Tavern Floor Sweeper</span></span><br>  Posts: 35<br> <font color=#6FB8DD>(8/15/03 8:18 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub40.ezboard.com/fthesaryrntavernthefurnace.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3474.topic&index=22>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: war on drus = failure</span><hr size=1> Why will people be more responsible.. because the government can inflict stricter laws if it is legal...<br>
<br>
Look at is this way<br>
<br>
Driving under the influence of Alcohol will get you a hefty fine and depending on the level of the of the Blood alochol.. revokation of your license.<br>
<br>
Just carrying 1 joint on you is considered a minor misdemeanor.  <br>
<br>
See something wrong with that?<br>
<br>
For something so damn illegal.. you can only get a misdemeanor for having one on you.. but yet if you have an open beer on you its a hefty fine and your license might get taken away. ( like i said, if your blood alcohol comes out high )<br>
<br>
Legalize the shit,  tax it.. control the influx.. BAM.  no more national debt.  give the stuff the usual sin tax.  Make a quarter cost as much as a pack of cigarettes... it will be so cheap and common that people wont do it as much because its readily available.<br>
<br>
Granted the current laws should still be in effect.  Make driving under the influence of Marijauna just as punishable as alcohol.<br>
<br>
Drug testing for Careers - hell yes.  I wouldnt want some half-wit to drop 1000lbs of steel drums on my head because he thinks its funny to do circles in the forklift.<br>
<br>
Drugs out of schools.  Yes.. make it just like alcohol.  18 or 21 and up.  License Revoked if you are caught underage in possession or buying.  <br>
<br>
It can be done.  Noone in the government wants to admit that they have been wrong all this time by literally throwing away our hard earned money so that Columbian drug lords think of new and inventive ways to get dope into the country.<br>
<br>
On a final note. lets think about this.<br>
<br>
lets say the sin tax on a quarter of marijauna is $.50<br>
so thats $2.00 per ounce.  $32 a pound.  <br>
<br>
now lets say every month 100,000 pounds of marijauna is shipped in.  thats 3.2 million dollars a month for the government .  averaging out to $42 million dollars a year in money the government can have.  Thats just on 100,000lb average.. could be more.. could be less.  And they could put a bigger sin tax on the stuff. <br>
<br>
In closing,  all i can say is that the government has gone about the war on drugs the WRONG way.  If they wanted to win and break the cartels.. legalize it.. it will become so common-place in no time that the risk vs reward for smuggling the stuff in wont be worth it anymore.<br>
<br>
Kryttos<br>
