This paragraph -- and its implication that people drive drunk because they enjoy driving drunk -- is some of the worst logic ever visited upon this poor, poor furnace.<br>
If, as Jangral claims, they really aim to drive as poorly as possible, one wonder why aren't already driving stoned.  Surely the legality can't be a barrier, since pot is easy to find and their eagerness to drive drunk proves they have no fear of the law.<br>
If alcohol were replaced overnight with pot, I would theorize that there would be less accidents relating to DUI, and if don't understand this, you've probably never smoked pot.  Marijuana knocks you on your ass compared to a beer (which is ultimately why I don't like it -- I'm too much of a control freak to give up my ego so easily.  Though it would probably be healthy for me, psychologically, to do so).  A great many people cited for DUI don't realize that they're above the legal limit, and a great many people in DUI-related accidents thought that they &quot;felt fine&quot; and would be able to drive normally.  I would expect these sorts of mistakes to be more rare while using pot.  Plus, it would mean I would have to get off this fucking couch.  And... uh... the couch.  Pass the salsa.<br>
