<br>
And yes, the legality is a barrier, since you can drink openly with other people in a public place like a restaurant or a bar, and until you start your car and put it in gear you haven't broken a single law. It's socially acceptable because it's legal and convenient to go have a few drinks with people after work or whatever. The issue is accessability to the substance, and regardless of how easy you say it is to get marijuana, the fact remains that unless you can go grab a dimebag off the shelf of a convenience store, it's still a hell of a lot harder to get pot than to get alcohol, simply because it is illegal. And in my book, that's a good thing. <br>
<br>
As it's been said, there's really no use arguing further on this, as most peoples' opinions are set in concrete. If you want to live in a world where narcotics are MORE accessible to the average person, then like I said before; it's your funeral... <p>Jangral<br>
