Ok, now we're communicating.  But if I enjoy getting drunk, why does it follow that I enjoy getting stoned?  As you say, people enjoy getting drunk; they will continue to enjoy getting drunk.  And the availability of pot does not affect pre-existing alcohol dependency.<br>
If there is no causal link -- i.e., you acknowledge that enjoyment of drink and enjoyment of pot are independent decisions and/or dependencies -- than arguments of the form &quot;how much easier&quot; (as in: &quot;all the alcoholics who drink every day...how much easier it would be to just smoke one little joint&quot;) make no sense. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#242422><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub40.ezboard.com/bthesaryrntavern.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nandarie>Nandarie</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><span style='color:orange;'>Tavern Resident</span></span><br>  Posts: 3329<br> <font color=#6FB8DD>(8/15/03 11:01 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub40.ezboard.com/fthesaryrntavernthefurnace.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3474.topic&index=30>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.mwscomp.com/movies/grail/jpgs/timencha.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: war on drus = failure</span><hr size=1> Ideally, there would be an efficient way to attack demand.  Since demand on marijuana is highly inelastic, lowering demand would be the only solution that would make a positive difference.  Attacking supply just raises the price, adding more profits to be made in the dealing business, without lowering use much.  Legalization would lower the price, and wouldn't cause that much more use of the drug, but that's not really accomplishing much either.  Lowering demand would reduse the number of people using and the price/profits would fall as well. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=205399"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://mywebpages.comcast.net/vicour1/NandSig.gif" style="bor