and <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=336005">Lagspike</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> too.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub40.ezboard.com/bthesaryrntavern.showUserPublicProfile?gid=numnayan>Numnayan</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle><span style='color:orange;'>Tavern Resident</span></span><br>  Posts: 2477<br> <font color=#6FB8DD>(8/15/03 11:24 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub40.ezboard.com/fthesaryrntavernthefurnace.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3474.topic&index=31>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.hneguild.com/Num/numbounceevil2.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: war on drus = failure</span><hr size=1> I would say that it is likely a good deal of the people who drive drunk do so because they are either alcoholics or just ashamed of their drinking, and consequently do not arrange for alternate transportation.  Most people I know do make an effort to have a designated driver when going out for social drinking.  There are, of course, the few idiots who think they're too strong for something as silly as alcohol to impair their driving, but those people are already idiots and dangerous pretty much by being in the car, sober or not.<br>
<br>
I have yet to meet anyone who smokes pot and is ashamed of it.  I don't actually <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>know</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> how much pot impairs your judgement, and unlike most people in this thread, and on the blast furnace in general, I won't pretend I do, but I would imagine the average pot-smoker would know they smoked too much, and have a buddy drive them home.<br>
<br>
People who have more experience with pot-smoking are more than welcome to offer their opinions, but as someone who drinks, sees other drinkers, and does, on occasion, go out drinking socially, and who does know a handful of pot-smokers, I'd really have to guess that a drinker is far more likely to put himself in a dangerous situation than a smoker.  I've never seen a rowdy high person.  I've never seen a surly or mean high person.  But maybe it's just my experience, and those opponents of legalization can give examples where they've seen otherwise.<br>
<br>
I mean, I'd rather have pot legal than alcohol.  Pot isn't physically addictive, I'm pretty sure it doesn't cause hangovers and other &quot;inconveniences&quot; alcohol can, and a smoker is a lot more likely to sit on his ass where is and not bother anyone than a drinker is.  Sure, I'd be pissed I couldn't drink anymore, but I don't really need to, and society would improve as a whole.<br>
<br>
I would suspect that a lot of the right-wing people, like Pecc, only know a couple of hippie losers he happened to see high by accident, and draw their opinions based on that.  I would imagine if any of his friends smoked pot, they wouldn't bother telling him because of the kind of person he is, and get together and have a good time without him.  I would further guess that he probably has friends, based on his beliefs, tone, and attitude, that are the kind of people to drink themselves stupid while alone, who have problems, won't get help, and drive and operate heavy machinery while intoxicated.<br>
<br>
A heavy drinker hides his habit from the world.  A heavy smoker lets everyone know about it.  That should tell you something about the psychology of both groups and which is less threatening.<br>
